<h2>1. Automated Propensity Scoring (Python · XGBoost)</h2>
<h4>What This Does – Plain English</h4>
<p>Harvard has 400K+ alumni. It's impossible to manually evaluate who might be ready to give a major gift. This script runs <strong>every night at 3am</strong> and produces a score (0–1) for each alumnus – like a credit score, but for philanthropic readiness. Monday morning, every gift officer gets a ranked list: <em>"These 50 people are most ready to hear from you this week."</em></p>
<div class="sflow">
  <div class="sbox"><div class="snum">Input</div><div class="stitle">Alumni Data</div><div class="sdesc">Giving history, events attended, wealth signals, email opens</div></div>
  <div class="sbox"><div class="snum">Model</div><div class="stitle">XGBoost AI</div><div class="sdesc">Trained on 10yrs of Harvard giving outcomes · 84% precision</div></div>
  <div class="sbox"><div class="snum">Output</div><div class="stitle">Priority List</div><div class="sdesc">Top 50 "ready now" prospects per gift officer</div></div>
  <div class="sbox"><div class="snum">Action</div><div class="stitle">Gift Officer</div><div class="sdesc">Uses list to book calls, visits, President trip stops</div></div>
</div>
<div class="chart-wrap sm" style="margin-bottom:16px" onclick="expandChart('autoAccChart','Propensity Model Accuracy FY22–FY26')"><div class="chart-label">Model Precision &amp; Prospects Surfaced – FY2022 to FY2026</div><div class="chart-hint">click to expand ↗</div><canvas id="autoAccChart"></canvas></div>
<h4>The Code</h4>
<pre><span class="c"># udas_propensity.py – nightly batch scoring (SYNTHETIC DEMO)</span>
<span class="k">import</span> pandas <span class="k">as</span> pd
<span class="k">import</span> xgboost <span class="k">as</span> xgb
<span class="k">from</span> sqlalchemy <span class="k">import</span> create_engine
<span class="k">from</span> sklearn.preprocessing <span class="k">import</span> StandardScaler
<span class="k">import</span> mlflow

ENG = create_engine(os.environ[<span class="s">"UDAS_WAREHOUSE"</span>])

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="n">load_features</span>():
    <span class="k">return</span> pd.read_sql(<span class="s">"""
        SELECT c.constituent_id,
               wp.estimated_capacity,    – DonorSearch + iWave ensemble
               wp.wealth_score,          – 1–10 normalized
               g.lifetime_giving,
               g.years_since_first_gift,
               g.gift_count_5yr,
               e.events_attended_3yr,
               e.email_open_rate,
               e.reunion_participation_flag,
               a.school_count,           – multi-school affiliation flag
               a.is_board_member,
               liq.liquidity_events_6mo  – IPO / M&A / vesting signal
        FROM constituent c
        LEFT JOIN wealth_profile wp    ON wp.constituent_id = c.constituent_id
        LEFT JOIN giving_summary g     ON g.constituent_id  = c.constituent_id
        LEFT JOIN engagement_summary e ON e.constituent_id  = c.constituent_id
        LEFT JOIN affiliation_rollup a ON a.constituent_id  = c.constituent_id
        LEFT JOIN liquidity_events liq ON liq.constituent_id = c.constituent_id
        WHERE c.deceased = false AND c.opt_out_modeling = false
    """</span>, ENG)

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="n">score</span>(df):
    <span class="k">with</span> mlflow.start_run(run_name=<span class="s">"udas-propensity-v3"</span>):
        model = xgb.XGBClassifier()
        model.load_model(<span class="s">"models/propensity_v3.json"</span>)
        X = StandardScaler().fit_transform(df.fillna(<span class="v">0</span>).drop(columns=[<span class="s">"constituent_id"</span>]))
        df[<span class="s">"p_5yr_gift"</span>]   = model.predict_proba(X)[:,<span class="v">1</span>]
        df[<span class="s">"p_principal"</span>]  = df[<span class="s">"p_5yr_gift"</span>] ** <span class="v">2.4</span>  <span class="c"># tail-weighted for $5M+ asks</span>
        df[<span class="s">"model_version"</span>] = <span class="s">"v3.1.2"</span>
        mlflow.log_metric(<span class="s">"rows_scored"</span>, len(df))
        mlflow.log_metric(<span class="s">"high_propensity_count"</span>, (df[<span class="s">"p_principal"</span>] > <span class="v">0.75</span>).sum())
    <span class="k">return</span> df[[<span class="s">"constituent_id"</span>, <span class="s">"p_5yr_gift"</span>, <span class="s">"p_principal"</span>, <span class="s">"model_version"</span>]]

<span class="k">if</span> __name__ == <span class="s">"__main__"</span>:
    out = score(load_features())
    out.to_sql(<span class="s">"propensity_score"</span>, ENG, if_exists=<span class="s">"replace"</span>, index=<span class="k">False</span>)
    print(<span class="s">f"✅ Scored {len(out):,} constituents. High-propensity: {(out.p_principal > 0.75).sum()}"</span>)</pre>
</div>

<div class="card cr-acc">
<h2>2. Wealth Screening Refresh – Ensemble Model</h2>
<h4>What This Does – Plain English</h4>
<p>We buy wealth data from three vendors (DonorSearch, iWave, WealthEngine). Sometimes they disagree wildly on a donor's estimated net worth. This script <strong>reconciles the three signals</strong> into a single trusted number, and flags any case where vendors disagree by more than 30% for a human researcher to review.</p>
<pre><span class="c"># wealth_ensemble.py – SYNTHETIC DEMO</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="n">blend_capacity</span>(ds: float, iw: float, we: float) -> dict:
    <span class="s">"""
    Median-of-three with disagreement alarm.
    If vendors disagree > 30%, flag for manual review queue.
    """</span>
    vals = sorted([v <span class="k">for</span> v <span class="k">in</span> [ds, iw, we] <span class="k">if</span> v <span class="k">is not None</span>])
    <span class="k">if not</span> vals:
        <span class="k">return</span> {<span class="s">"capacity"</span>: <span class="k">None</span>, <span class="s">"flag"</span>: <span class="s">"NO_DATA"</span>}
    median = vals[len(vals) // <span class="v">2</span>]
    spread = (max(vals) - min(vals)) / median <span class="k">if</span> median <span class="k">else</span> <span class="v">0</span>
    flag = <span class="s">"REVIEW_REQUIRED"</span> <span class="k">if</span> spread > <span class="v">0.30</span> <span class="k">else</span> <span class="s">"ACCEPTED"</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> {
        <span class="s">"capacity"</span>: round(median, <span class="v">-4</span>),  <span class="c"># round to nearest $10K</span>
        <span class="s">"flag"</span>: flag,
        <span class="s">"spread_pct"</span>: round(spread * <span class="v">100</span>, <span class="v">1</span>),
        <span class="s">"sources"</span>: {<span class="s">"donor_search"</span>: ds, <span class="s">"iwave"</span>: iw, <span class="s">"wealth_engine"</span>: we}
    }

<span class="c"># Example: $10M (DS), $8M (iWave), $12M (WE) → median $10M, 40% spread → REVIEW</span>
result = blend_capacity(<span class="v">10_000_000</span>, <span class="v">8_000_000</span>, <span class="v">12_000_000</span>)
<span class="c"># → {"capacity": 10000000, "flag": "REVIEW_REQUIRED", "spread_pct": 40.0}</span></pre>
</div>

