        <p style="font-size:.92rem;color:var(--mid);line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:18px">
          Most advancement shops know their pipeline by <em>stage</em>. Few know it by <em>fragility</em>. The Donor Fragility Index (DFI) cross-references every managed prospect's CRM profile with four real-time macroeconomic signals – VC funding velocity, public-market sector volatility, liquidity event calendars, and interest rate sensitivity – to produce a dynamic risk tier updated weekly. The result is not a static pipeline report; it is a <strong>forward-looking vulnerability map</strong> that allows gift officers and leadership to pre-position cultivation strategy before a market event forces a reactive pause.
        </p>

