      <!-- ----------------------------------------------------
           MODEL 2 · GEOPOLITICAL RISK & REPUTATIONAL BIOMETRICS
      -------------------------------------------------------- -->
      <div class="psws-wrapper" style="margin-bottom:28px">

        <div class="psws-header">
          <div class="psws-header-label">Model 2 · AI-Driven Pre-Solicitation Governance</div>
          <div class="psws-header-title">Geopolitical Risk &amp; Reputational Biometrics: The Pre-Solicitation Warning System</div>
          <p class="psws-header-sub">Ensuring every major ask is made to a donor whose current standing aligns with Harvard's institutional values – before the invitation is extended, not after.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="psws-body">

          <p style="font-size:.92rem;color:var(--mid);line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:22px">
            A transformational gift from a donor whose recent conduct contradicts Harvard's stated values – civil discourse, academic freedom, environmental responsibility, or human rights – can produce reputational damage that far exceeds the philanthropic benefit. Conversely, excessive caution that freezes legitimate major gift opportunities is its own strategic failure. The Pre-Solicitation Warning System (PSWS) resolves this tension through a structured, AI-assisted due diligence layer that runs automatically on every prospect at solicitation stage and on all managed prospects monthly.
          </p>

          <!-- Signal pipeline -->
          <h4 style="margin-bottom:14px;font-size:.85rem">Signal Architecture – How the System Works</h4>
          <div class="psws-pipeline">

            <div class="psws-stage">
              <div class="psws-stage-icon">
                <div class="psws-dot active"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="psws-content">
                <div class="psws-stage-label">Layer 1 · Data Ingestion</div>
                <div class="psws-stage-title">Multi-Source Signal Collection</div>
                <div class="psws-stage-desc">Automated daily feeds pull from global news APIs (Reuters, AP, BBC), SEC and regulatory filings, ESG rating updates (MSCI, Sustainalytics), sanctions databases (OFAC, EU), and social media sentiment indices. All signals are normalised against a 24-month baseline for the constituent.</div>
                <div class="psws-chips">
                  <span class="signal-chip">Reuters / AP / BBC feeds</span>
                  <span class="signal-chip">SEC / OFAC / EU sanctions</span>
                  <span class="signal-chip">MSCI ESG ratings</span>
                  <span class="signal-chip">Sustainalytics</span>
                  <span class="signal-chip">Social sentiment index</span>
                  <span class="signal-chip">Litigation tracker</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="psws-stage">
              <div class="psws-stage-icon">
                <div class="psws-dot gold"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="psws-content">
                <div class="psws-stage-label">Layer 2 · NLP Classification</div>
                <div class="psws-stage-title">Reputational Biometric Scoring</div>
                <div class="psws-stage-desc">A fine-tuned NLP classifier assigns each news event a category (controversy, philanthropy, governance failure, public statement, legal action) and a severity score. Events are weighted by source credibility, recency, and topical proximity to Harvard's seven core institutional values. A 30-day rolling composite score – the <strong>Reputational Biometric</strong> – is updated for each prospect.</div>
                <div class="psws-chips">
                  <span class="signal-chip">Event classification · 12 categories</span>
                  <span class="signal-chip">Harvard value alignment score</span>
                  <span class="signal-chip">Source credibility weighting</span>
                  <span class="signal-chip">30-day rolling composite</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="psws-stage">
              <div class="psws-stage-icon">
                <div class="psws-dot" style="background:var(--info);border-color:var(--info)"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="psws-content">
                <div class="psws-stage-label">Layer 3 · Human Review Gate</div>
                <div class="psws-stage-title">Prospect Research &amp; General Counsel Escalation</div>
                <div class="psws-stage-desc">Any amber or red signal triggers a mandatory Prospect Research desk review before the solicitation is cleared. For red flags involving litigation, regulatory action, or geopolitical controversy, the file is escalated jointly to the AVP and General Counsel's Office. <em>No 8-figure solicitation proceeds without a clean PSWS record for the preceding 90 days.</em></div>
                <div class="psws-chips">
                  <span class="signal-chip">Prospect Research desk review</span>
                  <span class="signal-chip">AVP sign-off required</span>
                  <span class="signal-chip">General Counsel escalation</span>
                  <span class="signal-chip">90-day clean record for 8-fig asks</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="psws-stage">
              <div class="psws-stage-icon">
                <div class="psws-dot green"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="psws-content">
                <div class="psws-stage-label">Layer 4 · CRM Integration</div>
                <div class="psws-stage-title">Solicitation Status Output → Gift Officer Briefing</div>
                <div class="psws-stage-desc">PSWS status is written back to the CRM as a standardised field visible to gift officers, the AVP, and VP. It appears automatically in the gift officer's weekly briefing pack and in all presidential trip preparation materials. A status change to amber or red removes the prospect from the current-quarter solicitation queue and generates a cultivation reset recommendation.</div>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>

          <!-- Status output panel -->
          <h4 style="margin-bottom:12px;margin-top:20px;font-size:.85rem">Pre-Solicitation Status Outputs</h4>
          <div class="psws-output">
            <div class="psws-status psws-st-green">
              <div class="psws-status-label">🟢 Cleared</div>
              <div class="psws-status-val">Proceed</div>
              <div class="psws-status-desc">No adverse signals in 90 days. Reputational Biometric ≤25. Solicitation may advance on gift officer's schedule.</div>
