            <p>The term "shadow endowment" is intentional: this is the philanthropic reserve that the institution does not formally count but can absolutely rely upon if the gift officer relationship has been properly maintained. The difference between a university that pauses in a crisis and one that advances is whether leadership has done this liquidity mapping <em>before</em> the disruption occurs. The time to identify your Tier 1 donors is not November 2008 – it is now.</p>
