  'kpi-raised':{t:'FY2026 Total Raised: $1.42B',s:'Monthly progress, current pace, and year-end expectation',b:`<div class="big-stat-grid"><div class="big-stat"><strong>$1.42B</strong><span>FY26 actual/projected</span></div><div class="big-stat green"><strong>+8.4%</strong><span>vs FY25 pace</span></div><div class="big-stat gold"><strong>84.2K</strong><span>gifts processed</span></div></div><h4>Monthly FY2026 Progress</h4>${monthBarsHtml([['Jul',88],['Aug',96],['Sep',126],['Oct',116],['Nov',121],['Dec',128],['Jan',132],['Feb',138],['Mar',150],['Apr',164],['May',171],['Jun',190]],190)}<p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--gray)">The monthly pattern shows why Q4 matters: leadership attention in April-June is expected to carry the largest close volume. For a new reader, this is the fundraising equivalent of a fiscal-year runway: current pace is healthy, but the year-end close still depends on principal-gift movement.</p>${mockNote()}`},
  'milestone-feasibility':{t:'Milestone 1: Campaign Feasibility Study',s:'Start now · public readiness by FY27',b:`${statsHtml([['15%','Complete'],['Owner','Strategy'],['Decision','Validate $10B+ capacity before launch']])}${timelineHtml([['Q3 FY26','Define top 200 interview pool and gift range assumptions.'],['Q4 FY26','Conduct confidential feasibility interviews with top households.'],['Q1 FY27','Deliver range, risks, and volunteer leadership plan.'],['FY27','Move qualified prospects into quiet-phase asks.']])}<p>For a new reader: a feasibility study tests whether Harvard has enough credible lead gifts, volunteer confidence, and case strength before announcing a campaign goal.</p>${mockNote()}`},
  'milestone-consensus':{t:'Milestone 2: Dean’s Consensus Tracker',s:'Build phase · cross-school prospect arbitration',b:`${statsHtml([['40%','Build progress'],['12 schools','Included in governance model'],['Weekly','Prospect conflict review cadence']])}${timelineHtml([['Design','Define shared prospect ownership rules.'],['Pilot','Run with HBS, HMS, FAS, SEAS.'],['Launch','VP office reviews priority conflicts weekly.'],['Scale','All schools use one arbitration dashboard.']])}<p>This prevents duplicate asks and helps the President see the whole relationship before engaging a donor.</p>`},
  'milestone-affinaquest':{t:'Milestone 3: Affinaquest CRM Rollout',s:'GSD, HGSE, HLS remaining · target Q4 FY26',b:`${statsHtml([['65%','Migration complete'],['3 schools','Remaining'],['30%','Projected gift velocity gain']])}${timelineHtml([['Data map','Confirm constituent, gift, pledge, and activity fields.'],['Migration','Move records and validate duplicates.'],['Training','Office hours for gift officers and managers.'],['Go-live','Parallel run, then cutover.']])}<p>New-reader note: CRM rollout is not just software; it is the operating system for prospect assignment, stewardship, and gift processing.</p>`},
  'milestone-wealth':{t:'Milestone 4: Wealth Screening Automation',s:'DonorSearch + iWave + WealthEngine ensemble',b:`${statsHtml([['55%','Pilot progress'],['380','Unmanaged $10M+ prospects surfaced'],['84%','Illustrative precision']])}${timelineHtml([['Pilot','Compare vendor signals against internal giving history.'],['Model','Blend capacity, engagement, liquidity, and affinity.'],['Assign','Route top 200 to gift officers.'],['Review','Measure conversion and false positives.']])}<p>Method: combine capacity estimates with behavior, not just net worth. This reduces noise and improves assignment quality.</p>`},
  'milestone-crm':{t:'Milestone 5: Unified CRM Phase II',s:'FAS, HBS, HMS · on track',b:`${statsHtml([['82%','Phase II complete'],['3 schools','High-volume units'],['Q3 FY26','Target delivery']])}${timelineHtml([['Integrate','Connect activities, proposals, gifts, and household records.'],['Test','Validate identities and pledge rollups.'],['Train','Manager dashboards and gift officer workflows.'],['Optimize','Retire duplicate reports.']])}`},
  'milestone-propensity':{t:'Complete: Propensity Model v3',s:'XGBoost deployed to all 12 schools',b:`${statsHtml([['100%','Deployment'],['7 factors','Recency, engagement, wealth, event, email, liquidity, network'],['Weekly','Score refresh']])}<p>Used to prioritize prospects for research, assignment, and presidential briefing. Human review remains required before major action.</p>`},
  'milestone-ai':{t:'Complete: Ethical AI Governance Charter',s:'Model cards, audit cadence, and human-in-loop review',b:`${statsHtml([['Quarterly','Disparate-impact audits'],['8-figure+','Human review required'],['Plain language','Explainability standard']])}<p>Best-practice reference logic: NIST AI Risk Management Framework, privacy-by-design, and advancement-sector ethical fundraising standards.</p>`},

